## Integrating this

Integrating this into an internal, larger system of applications would involve deploying the model on a server (with a cloud provider would be best practice but could also be on a physical machine that you or your team own). 1RM estimates could then be generated by making requests to the model's API using your analysis tool of choice (R, Python, Excel via Power Query, etc). From here, estimates could be integrated into the software or tools being used to program and monitor strength training and automated so they're current and available whenever they're needed.

## Conclusion

My simulated data might not align with the patterns in real training data, but I think the idea that some athletes can do heavy weight well while others do higher reps well is valid and should/can be captured when you're estimating 1RM from a submaximal set for max reps.
